===Verb===
{{en-verb|smells|smelling|'''[[smelled]]''' ''or'' '''[[smelt]]'''}}

# {{transitive}} To [[sense]] a smell or smells.
#: ''I can '''smell''' fresh bread.''
#: '''''Smell''' the milk and tell me whether it's gone off.''
# {{context|transitive|followed by '''like''' ''or'' '''of'''}} To have the smell (of).
#: ''His feet '''smell''' of cheese.''
#: ''The bum '''smelt''' like a brewery.'' <!-- Is 'smelt' only used negatively?-->
# {{intransitive}} To have a particular smell, whether good or bad.
#: ''The roses '''smell''' lovely.''

=====Synonyms=====
* (''sense a smell or smells''): [[detect]], [[sense]]
